<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>A second, unexpected answer</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Burn">Burn</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 1:10 p.m. 15/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> A second, unexpected answer<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/roleplay.cgi?read=358" TARGET=_self>Re: An Answer from the Druid</A> (Spiro)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>> "While my motives are my own to

<BR>&gt; understand, you can find comfort in knowing
<BR>&gt; I will help you as well as I can. But I can
<BR>&gt; only track her, if we find the place where
<BR>&gt; she landed, or by some strange luck just
<BR>&gt; cross her tracks."
<P>"One does not need luck when one has the power of the Darkness behind him."
<P>Spiro whirled in anger to see the origin of the deep voice that dared speak to him of the Darkness, while Grymm only glanced to it, not surprised in the least. There, where nothing was only a minute before, stood saw a tall figure wrapped in a black silken hooded cloak that was bound at the neck with a silver pentagram identical to the one held by Grymm Umbra. Only three such amulets existed, and the third was held by the Darkseer himself.
<P>Spiro's mouth opened in faint surprise, spewing the noise of silence. He only bowed his head and mumbled, "My lord Abaddon." Grymm stood and bowed. A formality only, though, born of respect and not rank. Umbra had fought with the Dark Prophet long enough to know that he was indeed human. The only thing unearthly about him was his wisdom.
<P>"You have need of me, my friend? The way you flew off back in Freeport I was certain you would have recovered the girl and slain whoever it was in your way in a manner most painful." Abaddon's shadowy face held a friendly, almost playful expression. Any onlooker who did not know the two men would have found it strange that a human could speak to a Tier'dal so openly and keep his hide.
<P>After all, Grymm's fascination with the art of flaying went a long distance.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
